SIMPLE: mogul
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mogul
<hw>Mo*gul"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the
Mongolian.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person of the Mongolian
race.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>Any of the Mongolian
peoples who conquered parts of India and established an empire lasting
from 1526 to 1857. Also, any of their descendents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Railroad)</fld> <def>A heavy locomotive for freight
traffic, having three pairs of connected driving wheels and a
two-wheeled truck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A great personage; magnate; autocrat; <as>as, an
industrial <ex>mogul</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Great Mogul</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Grand
Mogul</b></col></mcol>, <cd>the sovereign of the empire founded in
Hindustan by the Mongols under <persfn>Baber</persfn> in the sixteenth
century. Hence, a very important personage; a lord; -- sometimes only
<altname>mogul</altname> or <altname>Moghul</altname>.</cd></cs>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mogul</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Moghul</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mogul
<hw>Mo*gul"</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop.
a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Mogul</er>, <pos>n.</pos>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the Moguls{2}; <as>as, The Taj Mahal, the most beautiful
piece of <ex>Mogul</ex> architecture, was built by the <ex>Mogul</ex>
emperor <person>Shah Jehan</person> as a mausoleum for his favorite
wife</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mogul empire</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Moghul empire</ent>⟦br⟧
